item.title: What source is best?
item.dc:creator: @brandonscarinfo brandonscarinfo
item.description:
@brandonscarinfo wrote:

[quote=“shadytheone, post:8, topic:378153”]PI is bad for starters dude…
The codes used in ther, is completely diffrent then the other bases…[/quote]

You sir do not know how to code. PI is GREAT for starters… just because there are more tuts for delta than PI doesnt mean delta is better…

[quote=“Int Bauk, post:10, topic:378153”]All of those Servers you’ve mentioned are good.

100% correct my friend :).

I started Dodian and Learning conventions was difficult for me i didnt even know the differnce for the longest time…

I prefer Delta over PI onl because i know it really well but if you want the best stability i would choose PI

If you choose PI you wont run out of space like you do after a while with working with delta.

It’s possible too clean up delta, and make it a more stable server. The moderator deathchaos9 has done it. Look at his server development topic. He is fucking amazing.

It’s the case of, do you know your Java language enough to make it decent: combat, networking and stability.

When I first started Coding I used Delta, Devolution then Project Insanity, but it doesn’t matter which order/or what Source you choose, Devolution and Delta are fairly the same.
If you start Project Insanity before Delta then you won’t learn bad code/conventions and you’ll start to learn it easyer, where as if you used Delta first or Devolution you will learn this then move onto Project Insanity and find it’s fairly different, maybe even difficult.[/quote]

yes. deathchaos9 is GOD

When I first started Coding I used Delta, Devolution then Project Insanity, but it doesn’t matter which order/or what Source you choose, Devolution and Delta are fairly the same.
If you start Project Insanity before Delta then you won’t learn bad code/conventions and you’ll start to learn it easyer, where as if you used Delta first or Devolution you will learn this then move onto Project Insanity and find it’s fairly different, maybe even difficult.
